MOST of scripts for processing files depends on MGLtools scripts, in
order to make it work, they should point at correct path to MGLtools, 
as well as python modules for mgltools.

#1 setup MGLtools' python interpreter
MGLTools installation
download mgltools: http://mgltools.scripps.edu/downloads
tar -xvzf mgltools_x86_64Linux2_1.5.6.tar.gz
cd mgltools_x86_64Linux2_1.5.6/
./install.sh

After instalation of MGLtools
Export paths to python as:
#!/bin/bash

pwd1=/home/ahr/Desktop/HTVS-pipeline/utils
export PATH=$PATH:$pwd1/mgltools_x86_64Linux2_1.5.6/bin
export MGL=$pwd1/mgltools_x86_64Linux2_1.5.6
export MGLPY=$MGL/bin/python
export MGLUTIL=$MGL/MGLToolsPckgs/AutoDockTools/Utilities24/
source ~/.bashrc

then you can run $MGLPY as python interpreter.

